Pattern- Rolling Hash (Rabin-Karp)

Code-

var subStrHash = function(s, power, modulo, k, hashValue) {
    let n = s.length;
    let p = BigInt(power);
    let mod = BigInt(modulo);
    let target = BigInt(hashValue);

    let hash = 0n;
    let powerK = 1n;
    let resultIndex = 0;

    // compute p^k % mod
    for (let i = 0; i < k; i++) {
        powerK = (powerK * p) % mod;
    }

    for (let i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        let val = BigInt(s.charCodeAt(i) - 96);

        hash = (hash * p + val) % mod;

        if (i + k < n) {
            let removeVal = BigInt(s.charCodeAt(i + k) - 96);
            hash = (hash - (removeVal * powerK) % mod + mod) % mod;
        }

        if (n - i >= k && hash === target) {
            resultIndex = i;
        }
    }

    return s.substring(resultIndex, resultIndex + k);
};

----------------------------------------------------------


Problem-
Given string s, find substring of length k
Hash formula:
- (val(s[0]) * p^0 + val(s[1]) * p^1 + ... ) % modulo
Return first substring with given hashValue

Key Idea-
Compute hash efficiently using sliding window
Traverse from right to left to maintain powers easily

Important Trick-
Reverse sliding window
Maintain rolling hash:
-Remove last character
-Add new character at front

Steps-
Precompute powerK = p^k % modulo
Initialize:
-hash = 0
-resultIndex = 0
Traverse from right to left:
-Add current char to hash
-If window size > k:
   -Remove extra character
If window size == k:
 -If hash == target:
    -update result index
